        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'Open LOG_01_Fleet_Performance.xlsx in Excel for Web. Using Copilot in Excel, pull data from THREE tabs simultaneously — Fleet Utilisation by Region, On-Time Delivery Tracker AND Quarterly Cost-per-Kilometre — and build a new sheet called "QBR Fleet Dashboard". On that sheet, calculate for each of the 9 regions: absolute on-time variance vs target in percentage points, fleet utilisation gap vs target, year-on-year cost-per-km change, and quarterly run-rate of the deterioration. Add a group-level summary row at the top with KPI tiles for Group On-Time, Group Fleet Utilisation, and Number of Regions Below SLA. Insert a horizontal bar chart of on-time variance ranked worst to best, a clustered column chart of quarterly fleet utilisation by region, and a sparkline column for each region. Apply conditional formatting so on-time variance worse than -8 pp is red, -3 to -8 pp is amber, and better than -3 pp is green. The COO presents this to the QBR in 2 hours.'},
        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'Open LOG_04_Contract_Pipeline.xlsx in Excel for Web. Using Copilot in Excel, combine data from THREE tabs — Anchor Contract Health, Service-Credit Triggers AND Renewal Schedule — and create a new sheet called "Anchor Recovery Dashboard". Build a waterfall chart for each of the 3 service-credit anchors showing the movement from opening SLA score to closing SLA score across on-time, damage, and missed-pickup drivers. Beside each waterfall, add a service-credit exposure tile and a renewal-risk indicator. Sort the anchors from worst to best by SLA gap, highlight the 3 service-credit anchors in red banding, and embed a one-sentence summary text box beside each Red anchor. Apply conditional formatting so SLA score below 88% is red, 88-92% is amber, and above 92% is green. Output a QBR-ready dashboard sheet.'},
        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'Open LOG_06_Diesel_Cost_Schedule.xlsx in Excel for Web. Using Copilot in Excel, cross-reference the Diesel Cost Trend, Hedge Coverage AND Operating Margin Bridge tabs to create an early-warning tracker on a new sheet called "12-Week Cost Watchlist". Show diesel cost per km, hedge coverage ratio, operating margin variance, fleet utilisation, and SLA performance as 5 KPI tiles at the top. Below the tiles, build a line chart with secondary axis combining diesel cost per km (left axis, MYR) and operating margin variance (right axis, basis points) across the last 8 quarters. Add sparklines to each metric column so the QBR audience can scan trend at a glance. Apply conditional formatting so margin gap worse than -200 bp is red, -100 to -200 bp is amber, and better than -100 bp is green. Present as a compact RAG dashboard the MD can review weekly.'}
