    'Zava Mining Malaysia is a Malaysian-listed coal mining group with operating mines in East Kalimantan and South Sumatra producing 18 million tonnes per annum, three barging operations, two coal terminals, and 11 long-term offtake contracts covering Asian utilities. Newcastle thermal coal index fell 14% in the last quarter, two mines are running 9-12% below mine-plan strip ratio, royalty (PNBP) and IUP compliance correspondence with Kementerian ESDM has accelerated, KLHK has flagged a reclamation milestone slip on one of the East Kalimantan mines, and a community grievance at the South Sumatra haul-road has triggered a NGO advocacy campaign. September shipment commitments are at risk, two utility offtakers have requested re-pricing discussions, and Bursa Malaysia has asked for a clarification on disclosure timing. The Group MD walks into a Board sustainability and operations review in 7 days. The MD needs a defensible operations and ESG briefing pack, mine-by-mine variance analysis, regulator and offtaker holding lines, community remediation plan, and a 90-day production and sustainability stabilisation programme.',
