        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'Upload COAL_01_Mining_Operations.xlsx to Analyst. Across the Mine Production Tracker, Strip Ratio Performance AND Quarterly Cash Cost tabs, calculate the absolute and percentage variance against mine plan for each of the 6 mining areas, identify the 2 mines with the largest unfavourable strip-ratio variance and the production gap in tonnes, and quantify the group-level shortfall behind the September shipment risk. Build (1) a horizontal bar chart of strip-ratio variance by mine ranked worst to best, and (2) a 100% stacked column chart showing each mine\'s contribution to the production gap. Flag mines where strip-ratio variance is worse than -10% as Red, -3% to -10% as Amber, and above -3% as Green. Output as a RAG dashboard with both charts embedded and one recommended corrective action per Red mine.'},
        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'Upload COAL_04_Royalty_PNBP_Schedule.xlsx to Analyst. Cross-reference the Royalty Calculation, IUP Compliance Tracker AND Annual PNBP Reconciliation tabs to identify which mines have the largest royalty exposure under the ESDM audit, the cumulative under-paid royalty risk in MYR millions, and whether the deterioration accelerated in the last 6 months. Quantify the contribution of HBA reference price changes, calorific value adjustments, and overburden recovery, then build a waterfall chart for each at-risk mine showing Opening Royalty → HBA → CV Adjustment → Overburden → Closing Royalty. Present a structured RAG table with columns for Mine, Main Driver, 6-Month Change, ESDM Risk and Recommended Action, and embed the waterfall charts beneath it.'},
