        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'Open COAL_04_Royalty_PNBP_Schedule.xlsx in Excel for Web. Using Copilot in Excel, combine data from THREE tabs — Royalty Calculation, IUP Compliance Tracker AND Annual PNBP Reconciliation — and create a new sheet called "ESDM Audit Dashboard". Build a waterfall chart for each of the 2 mines under the largest royalty exposure showing the movement from opening to closing royalty across HBA, CV adjustment, and overburden drivers. Beside each waterfall, add a royalty exposure tile and an IUP compliance indicator. Sort the mines from worst to best by royalty gap, highlight the 2 highest-exposure mines in red banding, and embed a one-sentence summary text box beside each Red mine. Apply conditional formatting so royalty under-payment exposure above MYR 5M is red, MYR 1-5M is amber, and below MYR 1M is green. Output a Board-pack-ready dashboard sheet.'},
        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'Open COAL_05_Marketing_Pricing_Pack.xlsx in Excel for Web. Using Copilot in Excel, cross-reference the Newcastle Index Trend, Offtake Contract Health AND Cash Margin Bridge tabs to create an early-warning tracker on a new sheet called "12-Week Pricing Watchlist". Show Newcastle index, average realised price, cash margin per tonne, offtake fulfilment percentage, and spot-vs-contract mix as 5 KPI tiles at the top. Below the tiles, build a line chart with secondary axis combining Newcastle index (left axis, USD/t) and cash margin per tonne (right axis, USD/t) across the last 8 quarters. Add sparklines to each metric column so directors can scan trend at a glance. Apply conditional formatting so cash margin below USD 8/t is red, USD 8-15/t is amber, and above USD 15/t is green. Present as a compact RAG dashboard the CEO can review weekly.'}
